article.headline: Delaware 88, Marist 83
article.story: PISCATAWAY, N.J. -- Jawan Carter scored 25 of his career-high 30 points after halftime, including six straight foul shots in the final 28 seconds of overtime, to lead Delaware past Marist 88-83 Sunday in the Garden State Challenge at Rutgers. Alphonso Dawson had 18 of his 25 points in the second half and Marc Egerson added 23 points and 10 rebounds for Delaware, which finished 2-2 in the Challenge. Marist and Robert Morris were both 1-3 and Rutgers and St. Bonaventure finished 3-1. The Red Foxes got 21 points and seven assists from David Devezin, who played all 45 minutes, and 17 points and nine rebounds from Ryan Schneider. Dawson hit a layup with 35 seconds left in regulation to tie it at 72-72 and Marist missed two chances to win. In overtime, Egerson hit a layup with 3:57 left to give Delaware the lead for good. D.J. Boney made a key 3-pointer to make it 81-75, and Carter went 6-for-6 from the line.
